58.6	Capital_punishment_in_the_United_States	Capital punishment in the United States	The first recorded death sentence in the British North American colonies was carried out in 1608 on Captain George Kendall, who was executed by firing squad at the Jamestown colony for allegedly spying for the Spanish government.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/HuntsvilleUnitHuntsvilleTX.jpg/220px-HuntsvilleUnitHuntsvilleTX.jpg
